# Blueprint Protection File

**DO NOT DELETE THIS FILE OR PROJECT_BLUEPRINT.txt**

This file serves as a protection marker for the project blueprint.

## Protected Files
- PROJECT_BLUEPRINT.txt - The master project blueprint and source of truth

## Why This Exists
The PROJECT_BLUEPRINT.txt file is the single source of truth for the entire CarKid0 Rentals project. It contains:
- Complete project vision and story
- All feature specifications
- Hardware integration plans
- IoT implementation details
- Pan-African expansion strategy
- Business model and revenue streams
- Technical architecture
- Growth roadmap (5-year and 10-year plans)

## If You Need to Update the Blueprint
1. Open PROJECT_BLUEPRINT.txt
2. Make your changes
3. Save the file
4. Commit with message: "docs: update project blueprint - [brief description]"

## If the Blueprint is Accidentally Deleted
1. Check git history: `git log --all --full-history -- PROJECT_BLUEPRINT.txt`
2. Restore from git: `git checkout <commit-hash> -- PROJECT_BLUEPRINT.txt`
3. If not in git, check docs/archive/ for backups

## Blueprint Backup Strategy
- Primary: PROJECT_BLUEPRINT.txt (root directory)
- Git history: All versions tracked
- Documentation references: README.md, PROJECT_STATUS.md

